  "1": {
    "John Trapp": "The multitude being very great ] Yet not so great as the five thousand before fed with fewer loaves and more leavings. To teach us, that God\u2019s blessing, and not the quantity of meat, feeds and satisfies.\nVer.\n1. The multitude being very great] Yet not so great as the five thousand before fed with fewer loaves and more leavings. To teach us, that God\u2019s blessing, and not the quantity of meat, feeds and satisfies.\nVer.\n1. Onesiphorus was not ashamed of Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]`\u2019s chain at Rome, #2Ti 1:",
    "R. Alan Culpepper": "Feeding of the 5,000 (6:35-44)"
  },
