    "E.W. Bullinger": "When Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]` said, by the prophetic spirit, \"The three branches are three days.\nYet within three days shall Pharaoh lift up thine head,\" he meant \"days,\" not years; for we\nread: \"And it came to pass the third day,\" etc.;\u00a0 see Gen. xl. 12, 13,\nin the wilderness, Num. xiv. 33;\u00a0 \"forty days\" means forty days, and \"forty years\" means forty\nyears.\u00a0 So with Jonah; and the Lord, Matt. xii."
